#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&ksirk; is a computerized version of a well known strategy game. Commercial "
"and other Free Software versions exist but I (Gaël de Chalendar) created "
"this game initially as a C++ learning exercise and so, I developed it up to "
"this point (see <filename>README</filename> for details)."
msgstr ""
"&ksirk; je računalniška različica znane strateške igre. Komercialne in druge "
"različice brezplačne programske opreme obstajajo, vendar sem jaz (Gaël de "
"Chalendar) to igro prvotno ustvaril kot učno vajo C++ in sem jo razvil do te "
"točke (za podrobnosti glejte <filename>README</filename>)."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here's a screenshot of &ksirk;"
msgstr "Tu je posnetek zaslona &ksirk;"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the current version, &ksirk; is a multi-player network-enabled game with "
"an AI. (see <filename>TODO</filename> for details)"
msgstr ""
"V trenutni različici je &ksirk; omrežna igra za več igralcev z umetno "
"inteligenco. (za podrobnosti glejte <filename>TODO</filename>)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This documentation gives only the major information you need to start "
"playing. Please read the tooltips and the status bar messages to complete "
"your information."
msgstr ""
"Ta dokumentacija vsebuje le glavne informacije, ki jih potrebujete za "
"začetek igranja. Preberite nasvete orodij in sporočila v vrstici stanja, da "
"dopolnite svoje podatke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal of the game is simply to conquer the World... It is done by "
"attacking your neighbors with your armies. Peaceful, isn't it ? :-)"
msgstr ""
"Cilj igre je preprosto osvojiti svet ... To storite tako, da s svojimi "
"vojskami napadete svoje sosede. Mirno, kajne? :-)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &ksirk;"
msgstr "Uporaba &ksirk;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playing &ksirk;"
msgstr "Igranje &ksirk;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preliminary note: the map can be scrolled by three methods:"
msgstr "Predhodna opomba: po zemljevidu se lahko premikate na tri načine:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can put your mouse near a border of the window and the map will scroll "
"in that direction"
msgstr ""
"Miško lahko postavite blizu roba okna in zemljevid se bo pomaknil v to smer"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use your mouse wheel: with no modifier, it will scroll vertically; "
"when pressing the &Alt; key, it will scroll horizontally"
msgstr ""
"Uporabite lahko kolesce miške: brez modifikatorja se bo pomikalo navpično; "
"ko pritisnete &Alt; tipko, se pomika vodoravno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can use the keyboard arrows"
msgstr "Uporabite lahko puščice na tipkovnici"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting a game"
msgstr "Zagon igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "When &ksirk; starts, you are presented with a main menu."
msgstr "Ko se &ksirk; začne, se prikaže glavni meni."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "The main menu of &ksirk;"
msgstr "Glavni meni &ksirk;"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "Main menu"
msgstr "Glavni meni"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "New Local Game"
msgstr "Nova lokalna igra"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starts a new game."
msgstr "Začne novo igro."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "New Standard TCP/IP Network Game"
msgstr "Nova standardna omrežna igra TCP/IP"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start a new game using <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Internet_protocol_suite\">Internet protocol suite</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Začnite novo igro z uporabo <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Internet_protocol_suite\">zbirke internetnih protokolov</ulink>."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "Join Standard TCP/IP Network Game"
msgstr "Pridružite se standardni omrežni igri TCP/IP"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Join to the created by other user game using <ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_protocol_suite\">Internet protocol suite</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Pridružite se igri, ki jo je ustvaril drug uporabnik z <ulink url=\"https://"
"en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_protocol_suite\">zbirko internetnih "
"protokolov</ulink>."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Load…"
msgstr "Naloži…"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use this to load a previously saved game."
msgstr "Uporabite to za nalaganje predhodno shranjene igre."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:155 index.docbook:451
#, no-c-format
msgid "Quit"
msgstr "Zapusti"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:156
#, no-c-format
msgid "Maybe you finally don't want to play?"
msgstr "Mogoče končno nočete igrati?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you hit <guibutton>New Local Game</guibutton> you will be presented with "
"the <guilabel>New game properties</guilabel> dialog where you will be able "
"to choose the number of players, the skin (or theme) to use, the game type "
"(conquer the goal or have a specific goal) and finally if this game will be "
"played with online players or if it is purely local. New skins can be "
"downloaded using <guibutton>Download New Skins…</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Če pritisnete <guibutton>Nova lokalna igra</guibutton>, se vam prikaže "
"pogovorno okno <guilabel>Lastnosti nove igre</guilabel>, kjer boste lahko "
"izbrali število igralcev, preobleko (ali temo) za uporabo, vrsto igre "
"(osvojiti cilj ali imeti določen cilj) in končno, ali se bo ta igra igrala s "
"spletnimi igralci ali pa je izključno lokalna. Nove preobleke lahko "
"prenesete z gumbom <guibutton>Prenesi nove preobleke…</guibutton>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:163
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The New Game dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno Nova igra</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The New Game dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno Nova igra</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To start a TCP/IP network game, choose the <guilabel>New Standard TCP/IP "
"Network Game</guilabel> option on introduction screen. After pressing this "
"button you will be able to choose the network parameters: number of local "
"players and TCP port on which waiting for connections."
msgstr ""
"Če želite začeti omrežno igro TCP/IP, na uvodnem zaslonu izberite možnost "
"<guilabel>Nova standardna omrežna igra TCP/IP</guilabel>. Po pritisku na ta "
"gumb boste lahko izbrali omrežne parametre: število lokalnih predvajalnikov "
"in vrata TCP, na katerih čakate na povezave."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Network game parameters dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno s parametri omrežne igre</phrase>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Network game parameters dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno s parametri omrežne igre</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then, network players will be able to connect by choosing <guilabel>Join "
"Standard TCP/IP Network Game</guilabel> on the introduction screen and by "
"indicating the IP or hostname of the host and the port number you just set."
msgstr ""
"Nato se bodo omrežni igralci lahko povezali tako, da bodo na uvodnem zaslonu "
"izbrali <guilabel>Pridruži se standardni omrežni igri TCP/IP</guilabel> in "
"navedli IP ali ime gostitelja in številko vrat, ki ste jo pravkar nastavili."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:183
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Joining network game dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno za pridružitev omrežni igri</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Joining network game dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno za pridružitev omrežni igri</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each connection is indicated by a new row in the <guilabel>Players</"
"guilabel> table below the map thumbnail."
msgstr ""
"Vsaka povezava je označena z novo vrstico v tabeli <guilabel>Igralci</"
"guilabel> pod sličico zemljevida."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>New player row</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Nova vrsta igralca</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>New player row</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Nova vrsta igralca</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Let's suppose you keep all the default settings and hit <guibutton>Next</"
"guibutton>. You will then setup two players, one after one. For each one, "
"you'll choose a name, a nationality and, if you want, setup a password such "
"that nobody else than you can reuse this player when reloading this saved "
"game. Lastly, you will here specify if this player is played by the computer "
"or by a human being."
msgstr ""
"Recimo, da obdržite vse privzete nastavitve in pritisnete <guibutton>Naprej</"
"guibutton>. Nato boste enega za drugim postavili dva igralca. Za vsakega "
"boste izbrali ime, državljanstvo in, če želite, nastavili geslo, tako da "
"nihče drug kot vi ne more znova uporabiti tega igralca pri ponovnem "
"nalaganju te shranjene igre. Na koncu boste tukaj določili, ali tega igralca "
"igra računalnik ali človek."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The Player Setup dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno za nastavitev igralca</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:206
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The Player Setup dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno za nastavitev igralca</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then, after press <guibutton>Start</guibutton>, if you choose to play with "
"goal, the goal of each local player is displayed, preceded by a warning such "
"that other players looking at the same computer can discreetly turn away "
"while the goal is being viewed."
msgstr ""
"Potem, ko pritisnete <guibutton>Začni</guibutton>, če se odločite igrati z "
"golom, se prikaže gol vsakega lokalnega igralca, pred katerim je opozorilo, "
"tako da se lahko drugi igralci, ki gledajo v isti računalnik, diskretno "
"obrnejo stran, medtem ko gol je na ogled."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The Goal Display warning message</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Opozorilno sporočilo Prikaza cilja</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:216
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The Goal Display warning message</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Opozorilno sporočilo pri prikazu cilja</phrase>"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The Goal Display dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno za prikaz cilja</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The Goal Display dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno za prikaz cilja</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "Distribution"
msgstr "Distribucija"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the beginning of the game, countries are distributed to all the players. "
"Each country contains one army (represented by an infantryman) at the start. "
"Each player has some armies to distribute to his countries at their turn "
"(indicated by the presence of their name and their flag in the status bar). "
"Note that five armies are represented by a cavalryman and 10 by a cannon."
msgstr ""
"Na začetku igre so države razdeljene vsem igralcem. Vsaka država na začetku "
"vsebuje eno vojsko (ki jo predstavlja pehota). Vsak igralec ima nekaj vojsk, "
"ki jih razdeli svojim državam, ko pride na vrsto (kar je označeno z njegovim "
"imenom in zastavo v statusni vrstici). Upoštevajte, da pet vojsk predstavlja "
"konjenik, 10 pa top."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:234
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To put an army on one of your countries, click on it with the &LMB;. To "
"remove an army, click with the &RMB;. Note, as a general rule, that you will "
"never be able to remove more armies than the number you placed."
msgstr ""
"Če želite postaviti vojsko v eno od svojih držav, kliknite nanjo z &LMB;. Če "
"želite odstraniti vojsko, kliknite z &RMB;. Upoštevajte splošno pravilo, da "
"nikoli ne boste mogli odstraniti več vojsk od števila, ki ste ga postavili."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Placing armies</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Postavljanje vojsk</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Placing armies</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Postavljanje vojsk</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a player has distributed all there armies, the next player is "
"automatically selected to do the same task. When all players have finished "
"to distributing their armies, there is two possibilities that can be "
"selected by two buttons showed in the right panel:"
msgstr ""
"Ko igralec razdeli vse vojske, je naslednji igralec samodejno izbran za isto "
"nalogo. Ko vsi igralci končajo z razdelitvijo svojih vojsk, obstajata dve "
"možnosti, ki ju lahko izberete z dvema gumboma, prikazanima na desni plošči:"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid "Redistribution"
msgstr "Prerazporeditev"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "Recycle"
msgstr "Recikliranje"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One player wants to change some of his choices. The first player can then "
"remove an army he just put in a country with the &RMB; and put it in another "
"one with the &LMB;. When he finishes, he gives control to next player with "
"the <guibutton>Valid</guibutton> button. When all players have finished "
"their redistribution, the two buttons are displayed again."
msgstr ""
"En igralec želi spremeniti nekaj svojih izbir. Prvi igralec lahko nato "
"odstrani vojsko, ki jo je pravkar postavil v državo z &RMB; in jo vstavite v "
"drugo z &LMB;. Ko konča, prepusti nadzor naslednjemu igralcu z gumbom "
"<guibutton>Veljavno</guibutton>. Ko vsi igralci končajo s prerazporeditvijo, "
"se gumba ponovno prikažeta."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid "End of redistribution"
msgstr "Konec redistribucije"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid "Done"
msgstr "Končano"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "The redistribution is finished and the game can continue."
msgstr "Prerazporeditev je končana in igra se lahko nadaljuje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:272
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fight"
msgstr "Bitka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the redistribution, a turn starts. Each player plays at his turn. He "
"has the choice to:"
msgstr ""
"Po prerazporeditvi se začne obrat. Vsak igralec igra na svoji vrsti. Na "
"izbiro ima:"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Next player"
msgstr "Naslednji igralec"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid "Next Player"
msgstr "Naslednji igralec"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:285
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The turn of the current player finishes and it's the turn of the next one."
msgstr "Poteza trenutnega igralca je končana in na vrsti je naslednji."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:292
#, no-c-format
msgid "Attack 1"
msgstr "Napad 1"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&nbsp; <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"attackTwo.png\" "
"format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> <textobject><phrase>Attack 2</phrase></"
"textobject> </inlinemediaobject>&nbsp; <inlinemediaobject> "
"<imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"attackThree.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></"
"imageobject> <textobject><phrase>Attack 3</phrase></textobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Attack with one, two or three armies</"
"guibutton>&nbsp; <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref="
"\"autoattack.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> <textobject><phrase>Auto "
"attack</phrase></textobject> </inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Auto attack</"
"guibutton>"
msgstr ""
"&nbsp; <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"attackTwo.png\" "
"format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> <textobject><phrase>Napad 2</phrase></"
"textobject> </inlinemediaobject>&nbsp; <inlinemediaobject> "
"<imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"attackThree.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></"
"imageobject> <textobject><phrase>Napad 3</phrase></textobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Napad z eno, dvema ali tremi vojskami</"
"guibutton>&nbsp; <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref="
"\"autoattack.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> "
"<textobject><phrase>Samodejni napad</phrase></textobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Samodejni napad</guibutton>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To attack, drag with the mouse from the attacking country and drop to the "
"attacked one. You will then be presented with a contextual menu showing the "
"above entries."
msgstr ""
"Za napad povlecite z miško iz napadajoče države in spustite na napadeno. "
"Nato se vam prikaže kontekstni meni, ki prikazuje zgornje vnose."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Attack menu</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Meni napada</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Attack menu</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Meni napada</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For a country X to attack a country Y with x armies, 2 conditions must be "
"fulfilled:"
msgstr ""
"Da država X napade državo Y z x vojskami, morata biti izpolnjena 2 pogoja:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "the two countries must be neighbors;"
msgstr "državi morata biti sosedi;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid "country X must have at least x+1 armies before the attack."
msgstr "država X mora imeti vsaj x+1 armado pred napadom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the attack is valid, a dialog is displayed if necessary for the defender "
"to choose if he wants to defend with one or two armies or let the computer "
"decide."
msgstr ""
"Če je napad veljaven, se po potrebi prikaže pogovorno okno, v katerem lahko "
"branilec izbere, ali se želi braniti z eno ali dvema vojskama ali naj odloči "
"računalnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the defenders choice is done, the fight will occur and be completed. "
"This will described below."
msgstr ""
"Ko je izbira branilcev opravljena, bo prišlo do boja in bo končan. To bo "
"opisano spodaj."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:335
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Defense dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno obrambe</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Defense dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno obrambe</phrase>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:348
#, no-c-format
msgid "Move armies"
msgstr "Premakni vojske"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:350
#, no-c-format
msgid "Move Armies from one country to another"
msgstr "Premakni vojske iz ene države v drugo"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:353
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the last action of a player's turn. It gives the possibility to move "
"some armies from one of his country to another, neighboring the first one. "
"To choose the two countries, please drag and drop like you use during an "
"attack. When both countries are selected, a slider is displayed on which you "
"can choose how many armies there will be on each country afterwards."
msgstr ""
"To je zadnje dejanje na potezi igralca. Daje možnost premikanja nekaterih "
"vojsk iz ene njegove države v drugo sosednjo prvo. Če želite izbrati dve "
"državi, povlecite in spustite, kot to uporabljate med napadom. Ko sta "
"izbrani obe državi, se prikaže drsnik, na katerem lahko nato izberete, "
"koliko vojsk bo potem v posamezni državi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid "Outcome of the fight"
msgstr "Izid bitke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For each army in the fight there is a corresponding die cast. The player who "
"rolls a higher number on the dice, whether being from the attacker or "
"defender, wins and the one to roll a smaller number on the dice loses armies "
"according to the number of dice thrown."
msgstr ""
"Za vsako vojsko v boju obstaja ustrezen met kock. Igralec, ki vrže večje "
"število na kocki, ne glede na to, ali je napadalec ali branilec, zmaga, "
"tisti, ki vrže manjše število na kocki, pa izgubi vojske glede na število "
"vrženih kock."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:364
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Attack result displayed</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Prikaz rezultata napada</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:367
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Attack result displayed</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Prikaz rezultata napada</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the number of armies in the defender country reaches 0, the ownership of "
"this country changes to the attacker: his flag is set up and one of his "
"attacking armies is installed in his new country. The \"Move armies\" slider "
"is displayed as for the moves of the end of the turn."
msgstr ""
"Če število armad v državi branilca doseže 0, se lastništvo te države "
"spremeni v napadalca: njegova zastava je postavljena in ena od njegovih "
"napadalnih armad je nameščena v njegovi novi državi. Drsnik \"Premakni vojske"
"\" je prikazan kot za poteze na koncu poteze."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:374
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Invasion slider</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Drsnik invazije</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:377
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Invasion slider</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Drsnik invazije</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid "End of the turn"
msgstr "Konec poteze"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:385
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To finish your current turn, if you don't want to move armies, you can hit "
"the <guibutton>Next Player</guibutton> button in the toolbar."
msgstr ""
"Da bi končali svojo trenutno potezo, če ne želite premakniti vojske, lahko "
"pritisnete gumb <guibutton>Naslednji igralec</guibutton> v orodni vrstici."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:387
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When everybody has played, the turn is finished. Some armies are distributed "
"to the players, in function of the countries they own: 1 for each group of "
"three countries, with a minimum of 3. There is also a bonus for players that "
"own a complete continent, different for each one. The values of the bonuses "
"for the default skin are:"
msgstr ""
"Ko so vsi igrali, je poteza končana. Nekatere vojske so razdeljene igralcem "
"glede na državo, ki jo imajo v lasti: 1 za vsako skupino treh držav, z "
"najmanj 3. Obstaja tudi bonus za igralce, ki imajo v lasti celoten "
"kontinent, za vsakega drugačen. Vrednosti bonusov za privzeto preobleko so:"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:390
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bonus due to the continents"
msgstr "Bonus zaradi kontinentov"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid "Continent"
msgstr "Kontinent"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:395
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bonus"
msgstr "Bonus"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:399
#, no-c-format
msgid "North America"
msgstr "Severna Amerika"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:399 index.docbook:401
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>5</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>5</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:400
#, no-c-format
msgid "South America"
msgstr "Južna Amerika"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:400 index.docbook:404
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>2</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>2</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:401
#, no-c-format
msgid "Europe"
msgstr "Evropa"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid "Africa"
msgstr "Afrika"

